---
source: crates/webpkit-cli/tests/snapshot.rs
expression: "help(\"webp\", \"--help\")"
---
Command-line tools for the webpkit WebP codec: libwebp-style cwebp (lossy by default, -lossless for VP8L) / dwebp and the webp brand tool.

Usage: webp [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  decode   Decode a WebP VP8L file to PNG (default), PPM/PAM, or raw pixels
  encode   Encode a PNG/PPM/PAM/raw image into a WebP file (lossless, or --lossy)
  convert  Batch-convert many images (or directories) to WebP, in parallel
  info     Print a summary of a WebP file (size, alpha, metadata, animation)
  help     Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -v, --verbose...  Print per-stage detail on stderr
  -q, --quiet       Suppress all non-error output
  -h, --help        Print help
  -V, --version     Print version
